1
00:00:16,220 --> 00:00:18,950
♪Passing by where leaves fall
and flowers fade♪

2
00:00:18,950 --> 00:00:21,450
♪Chancing upon shooting stars
and northern lights♪

3
00:00:21,450 --> 00:00:24,660
♪At this moment, I borrow the wind♪

4
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:26,320
♪To set sail for distant seas♪

5
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:29,120
♪Rumors swirl close to my ears♪

6
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:31,650
♪Some laugh and say my dreams are wild♪

7
00:00:31,650 --> 00:00:34,900
♪Yet I will not change
my original aspiration♪

8
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:36,900
♪Even if it means running into a wall♪

9
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:39,150
♪I know the road
to growing up brings pain♪

10
00:00:39,410 --> 00:00:41,880
♪Still, I hold fast
to the dream I cherish♪

11
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:44,490
♪Never have I thought to yield♪

12
00:00:44,490 --> 00:00:46,720
♪Youth is meant
to stand against the world♪

13
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:47,990
♪I've always longed♪

14
00:00:47,990 --> 00:00:49,580
♪To stand upon the highest peak♪

15
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:50,570
♪I've always wished♪

16
00:00:50,570 --> 00:00:52,180
♪To cross a river wide and deep♪

17
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:55,800
♪In darkness,
look up to see the sky turn clear♪

18
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,240
♪Unyielding♪

19
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:59,780
♪The butterfly reborn
from its cocoon must fly♪

20
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:03,320
♪Like bamboo breaking forth,
I chase dreams through hardship♪

21
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:06,190
♪Return to me, my dream♪

22
00:01:06,190 --> 00:01:07,430
♪Unyielding♪

23
00:01:07,430 --> 00:01:09,980
♪My pure heart stays the same♪

24
00:01:09,980 --> 00:01:10,980
♪You must face the wind♪

25
00:01:10,980 --> 00:01:13,520
♪And go where your heart leads♪

26
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:16,560
♪Embrace the moonlight
that belongs to you♪

27
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:18,040
♪In the dark♪

28
00:01:18,060 --> 00:01:21,500
=Voyage to Haihun, Season 2=

29
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:23,300
=Episode 16=

30
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,930
Imperial Guard Commander Wang Heng,
receive the decree.

31
00:01:34,350 --> 00:01:35,680
See for yourself.

32
00:01:36,070 --> 00:01:38,510
State affairs are beyond my rank.

33
00:01:42,010 --> 00:01:44,460
Decree to Commander Heng
of the Huben Army,

34
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:47,870
I am mindful of spies from Xiqiang
sneaking into Yuzhang,

35
00:01:48,290 --> 00:01:50,070
hearing that you investigated in person,

36
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:50,950
exerting great effort.

37
00:01:51,510 --> 00:01:52,790
I'm deeply gratified.

38
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,000
I send this decree to ask about it.

39
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,120
How is the progress?

40
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:58,120
Have you uncovered their plot

41
00:01:58,220 --> 00:01:59,480
or capture the traitor?

42
00:01:59,580 --> 00:02:02,040
I know you are skilled in such affairs.

43
00:02:02,050 --> 00:02:03,100
Your prestige is unmatched.

44
00:02:03,470 --> 00:02:05,220
Thus, return to Chang'an at once,

45
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:06,200
take command of the army,

46
00:02:06,370 --> 00:02:07,470
and march against Xiqiang.

47
00:02:07,690 --> 00:02:09,280
I hope you will not fail my expectations.

48
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:11,200
Sweep away the rebels.

49
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,250
Bring peace to the people.

50
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:14,120
Show the might of the Great Han.

51
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,240
Moreover,

52
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:16,870
we have been apart for long.

53
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:18,110
My longing for you

54
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:19,360
is beyond words.

55
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,090
Once you receive this decree,

56
00:02:21,090 --> 00:02:22,060
return without delay.

57
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:24,300
I wish to see you in person

58
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,040
and discuss affairs of the realm.

59
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,070
I can continue investigating

60
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,770
Xiqiang spies with Lord Sun.

61
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,960
The realm faces troubles

62
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,200
and you should reply.

63
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,400
Reply on my behalf.

64
00:02:35,730 --> 00:02:36,590
To what?

65
00:02:37,910 --> 00:02:38,850
The letter, of course.

66
00:02:38,870 --> 00:02:40,310
Write back whatever you see

67
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,020
and whatever comes to mind.

68
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,500
In my voice, as if I spoke it.

69
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:47,990
Bring the brush

70
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:48,960
and the ink.

71
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:11,010
Your Majesty,

72
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,400
I traveled in secret to gather news.

73
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:14,870
Roaming across Yuzhang,

74
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:17,030
I saw the common folk suffering.

75
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,470
My heart remained heavy.

76
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:20,700
Women clutching children fled in panic.

77
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,720
They had nothing to eat.

78
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:23,960
Cries of misery echoed.

79
00:03:24,490 --> 00:03:26,150
It was heartbreaking to witness.

80
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:28,400
The magistrate lost
in folly and neglect,

81
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,520
imposing excessive and arbitrary taxes,

82
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,700
leaving people in misery.

83
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:34,040
(A cute young man; a fine match for me.)
There were

84
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,470
corrupt schemers who fabricated

85
00:03:35,470 --> 00:03:36,670
false charges upon the people,

86
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,310
driving them into hard labor.

87
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,470
The people were treated like slaves.

88
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:43,330
Such acts are beyond outrage.

89
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:44,800
These officials

90
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:46,530
showed no care for the people's plight

91
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:48,280
and shielded each other from blame,

92
00:03:48,410 --> 00:03:49,810
treating the common folk like weeds.

93
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:51,630
I was met with obstruction

94
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:53,610
while speaking out for the people.

95
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,310
The voice of justice cannot spread.

96
00:03:56,730 --> 00:03:58,230
All these strange occurrences

97
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,190
bear traces of Xiqiang people.

98
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,620
What's more,

99
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,470
there is a sorceress from Xiqiang

100
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:04,760
who beguiles the people

101
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:06,080
with deceitful words.

102
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,710
The common folk lose their true nature

103
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:09,590
and follow twisted beliefs blindly.

104
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,900
Truly a sorrow for the world.

105
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:15,100
Yet I have not captured the mastermind.

106
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:18,200
Could these culprits
be spies of Xiqiang?

107
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,110
No solid proof is yet in my hands.

108
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:25,320
Thus, I choose to stay in Haihun
with Liu He,

109
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,810
to continue hunting the mastermind,

110
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:31,840
to uphold Your Majesty's benevolent rule,

111
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,300
to govern well,

112
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:34,560
to save people,

113
00:04:35,020 --> 00:04:35,960
to lighten taxes,

114
00:04:36,290 --> 00:04:37,390
and to grant people peace.

115
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:38,970
So with all hearts united,

116
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:41,220
we forge the Great Han's era.

117
00:04:41,850 --> 00:04:43,480
(Wang Heng)
When the truth is revealed,

118
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:44,970
I shall return to court.

119
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,640
Heng.

120
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:52,460
Then how can we reveal the truth?

121
00:04:58,630 --> 00:04:59,470
Melody, rhythm,

122
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,520
rock.

123
00:05:01,940 --> 00:05:03,840
Milords, forgive my late welcome.

124
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:07,310
I heard you came
under His Majesty's command

125
00:05:07,590 --> 00:05:09,160
to show care for the vulnerable

126
00:05:09,470 --> 00:05:11,310
observe local customs and ways,

127
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,180
examine the governance of the officials,

128
00:05:13,270 --> 00:05:15,200
and discover and recommend worthy talents.

129
00:05:15,790 --> 00:05:17,390
I shall give my utmost effort

130
00:05:17,470 --> 00:05:18,920
to serve at your disposal.

131
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,310
Much obliged, Lord Sun.

132
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,320
Lord Sun.

133
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,070
Madam Qingge.

134
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,360
It has been too long.

135
00:05:29,870 --> 00:05:30,710
Where is the Marquis?

136
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,580
Well...

137
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:34,720
La la la la la.

138
00:05:34,950 --> 00:05:37,120
La la la la.

139
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:37,880
Stop.

140
00:05:42,350 --> 00:05:44,040
That doesn't feel rock and roll enough.

141
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:47,070
Then how should I rock and roll

142
00:05:47,070 --> 00:05:48,240
to reach your standard?

143
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,310
Good question.

144
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,920
It really gets to the heart of the band.

145
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:56,360
Rock and roll is about letting loose.

146
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:58,530
Speak straight from the heart.

147
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:02,660
Ahem.

148
00:06:04,350 --> 00:06:07,920
La la la la la la la la.

149
00:06:07,940 --> 00:06:09,330
This just got worse.

150
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:14,080
La la la la la la la la.

151
00:06:14,890 --> 00:06:16,750
Qingge, when did you get back?

152
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:19,260
Looks like you're having fun

153
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:20,290
while I was away.

154
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:22,240
Just in time to join our band.

155
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:24,370
Let's go over there.

156
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:26,370
This one looks nice.

157
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,070
A touch of red on the branch.

158
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,920
A few wishes on the cloth.

159
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:33,780
This is the check-in spot
Heng had in mind.

160
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,320
The check-in spot?

161
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,600
Lately, you've been picking up

162
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,070
quite a few new words from Wang.

163
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:42,680
I don't know well.

164
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,080
All I know is a single red cord

165
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:47,520
and a piece of silk cloth
can carry a wish.

166
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,460
Sir, I'll take this one.

167
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:57,390
Is Lord Yan in good health?

168
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,880
Safe and sound.

169
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:02,430
He's commanded to march against Xiqiang.

170
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:03,770
He's preparing for it.

171
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:06,270
He is a straightforward man.

172
00:07:06,650 --> 00:07:09,040
Tell him not to let pride guide him
on the battlefield.

173
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,430
He's changed quite a bit.

174
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:13,040
With the passing years,

175
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,350
he's grown gentler.

176
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:19,000
We talked till dawn when I returned.

177
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:23,630
It felt like we made up
for all the years of silence.

178
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,510
It's truly wonderful.

179
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:28,480
Truly wonderful.

180
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:34,070
I mean it.

181
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,070
Come, take a look at my wishing tree.

182
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,430
It's quite magical.

183
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:43,900
Is this tree enchanted?

184
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,650
We'll know once we try.

185
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,260
Welcome.

186
00:07:50,290 --> 00:07:52,240
Write your wishes on this cloth strip.

187
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,240
Then hang it on the tree.

188
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:54,910
Your wishes will surely come true.

189
00:08:00,670 --> 00:08:01,630
No peeking.

190
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:25,080
May the Great Han prosper

191
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,310
and Lord Yan return victorious.

192
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,400
What about yours?

193
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:35,720
Mine's the same.

194
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,150
And may all of us

195
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,300
gather again in Chang'an.

196
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,800
Oh, right.

197
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:49,590
You must join our band.

198
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:50,960
Rock.

199
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:52,580
Rock?

200
00:08:53,420 --> 00:08:54,390
(Melon: Summer Music)

201
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:55,790
All ticket holders

202
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:57,150
get one free painting session.

203
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:59,390
Guard your gold and silver well.

204
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,580
Such a grand scene.

205
